fields.title: Python Project
fields.overview: Welcome to Python for Beginners, a project-based approach to learning web development with the Python (Django).

fields.title: Setting and instruments
fields.description:
We start by properly covering how to configure a local development environment in
Chapter 1. We’re using bleeding edge tools in this book: the most recent version of
Django (3.0), Python (3.7), and Pipenv to manage our virtual environments. We also
introduce the command line and discuss how to work with a modern text editor
